b'       Dear Students,        Link      POSTECH International Exchange Program for the 2017 Spring semester (FEBJUN, 2017)    1. Eligibility : Undergraduate or graduate students nominated by the international office of partner universities.    2. Requirements  1) CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) of B or above 2) English Proficiency: TOEFL iBT 79, IELTS (Ac) 6.0, or above (for nonnative English speakers only)  It may be substituted with equivalent proof documents approved by an exchange coordinator at home university (ex. certificate, letter, test score sheet, etc.)  3. Nomination Period : September 1~10, 2016  4. Nomination Procedure Kindly submit the Letter of Approval (signed by Faculty Advisor & HoD) and a copy of your passport at the Office of International Relations. Also submit your nomination by completing the attached excel file (nomination sheet) and send it to  oir4@wmail.iitm.ac.in oir4.iitm@gmail.com September 10, 2016  5. Deadline for Submission of Online Application: September 30, 2016  6. Link to the Online Application:    7. Supporting Documents to Prepare 1) Transcript of Academic Records in English 2) Official Score of English Proficiency (for nonnative English speakers only) 3) One Recommendation Letter from Home University Supervisor 4) Copy of Passport 5) Letter of Support (for research exchange only)  8. How to Submit the Application Documents </b All supporting documents in PDF will be uploaded on the online application system. After completing the online application process, nominees should print out the completed application form, sign on it and submit the signed application form to the designated outbound exchange coordinator at home university. Then, the application form (PDF) will be sent to POSTECH by the outbound exchange coordinator no later than October 1, 2016 .  9. Outcome Announcement: by the end of November, 2  10. Advising Professor All exchange students are required to identify a supervising professortobe at POSTECH on the application form. Please find 3 professors from the departments so that POSTECH can find an available professor among the lists. The advising professors will determine nominees admissions and approve course registrations.     Mr. Arvind Sivamani  Liaison Officer (Outgoing Students)  International Relations  Office of International Relations l 2 nd Floor, IC & SR Building  Indian Institute of Technology Madras l Chennai  600 036 l INDIA  Tel: (91) 0442257 4928  Email: oir4@wmail.iitm.ac.in   Website:    '

